        <h2>XSS Prevention Tips for Users</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Be Cautious with Links:</strong> Avoid clicking on suspicious links or attachments, especially from unknown sources. If something looks unusual, double-check the sender and the content.</li>
            <li><strong>Don’t Share Personal Info:</strong> Never share sensitive personal information like your email, phone number, or address in public comments or posts.</li>
            <li><strong>Avoid Entering Scripts or Code:</strong> Don't copy and paste scripts or code into comments or posts, even if someone claims it’s “fun” or “cool.” These could be harmful.</li>
            <li><strong>Report Suspicious Content:</strong> If you notice strange or spammy comments, report them to the platform. This can help prevent others from becoming victims.</li>
            <li><strong>Keep Software Updated:</strong> Always keep your browser and apps up to date, as updates often include important security fixes.</li>
            <li><strong>Enable Two-Factor Authentication:</strong> Protect your account with two-factor authentication (2FA) to reduce the risk of unauthorized access.</li>
            <li><strong>Think Before You Click:</strong> When in doubt, avoid clicking on pop-up ads or sketchy-looking websites. Some may have malicious intent.</li>
        </ul>
